BEGIN_TEXT
Use the Laws of logarithms to rewrite the expression
\[
\ln \sqrt[$a]{x y}
\]
in a form with no logarithm of a product, quotient or power.
$BR
After rewriting we have
\[
\ln \sqrt[$a]{x y}= A \ln x + B \ln y
\]
$BR
with the constant
$BR
\(A=\) \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
and the constant
$BR
\(B=\) \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = 1/$a;
$ans2 = 1/$a;

